response.original_title: Brady Street: Portrait of a Neighborhood
response.overview: In the 1960s and '70s, Brady Street became a thriving hub of counterculture—a legacy that persists in Milwaukee today.  Like many neighborhoods, Brady Street has faced its share of decline. But by the end of the 20th century, determined  community efforts sparked a renaissance, revitalizing the area and transforming it into a diverse urban haven. Longtime resident Julilly Kohler puts it best: "It’s people that make the street. It’s really about people and getting people involved."
response.title: Brady Street: Portrait of a Neighborhood
